Abstract = {{The presented work is part of a more extensive study of the entropy of
   the radiation field and its vertical variation in the climate system.
   The vertical variation in the long-wave with liquid water clouds is
   shown here. The entropy of the radiation field is separated into a
   reversible and an irreversible term, and the effect of varying cloud
   height and optical thickness on each term is examined. The results show
   that in the long-wave spectrum, the behaviour of the reversible
   component is very similar to the entropy of the radiation field.
   However, as the cloud height and optical thickness are increased, the
   irreversible component becomes more significant.}},
